<subSubSection id="4E178A0F56194035416D9616B40884DD" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="F3677EC1D70C0A9EA86057F3744E22BB" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="07425BBB8A9B3FD76E77A5D974DCD221" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">
Flowering heads large; fruiting calyx vesicular, turbinate, shining, netted-nerved, calyx teeth with base not ciliolate; corolla longer than calyx, seeds sub-globular, light brown (
<figureCitation id="AFF715A292354CE8100D87A5B4EF5F0E" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">Figures 2A</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="A1874C4A9812BF16F35D94BA3EF59305" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Trifolium vesiculosum collected in Viterbo (bar = 1 mm). Flowers (4 July 2016), pod and seeds (2 August 2016)." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106592" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure5">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9A9895F3DB5126F593F7AF85AD5957B" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C1DD91986FE5BBB1875C4EAD1A167533" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Updated geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0BF5B60C0EC35CF2C992BD2E08A9E120" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Tuscany: +, Umbria: +, Lazio: +, Abruzzo: +, Campania: +, Apulia: 0 (new), Basilicata: 0 (new), Calabria: 0 (new), Sicily: 0 (new), Sardinia: +.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0090C08618A50A4B8458FCF2F00375DB" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph id="43950299A3B743D36704B5C539270B0B" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8708B96E0656623F858E0E99908A2FA9" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">
It is a Mediterranean species growing from southern to central Europe on fertile, well-drained soils. This clover is cultivated on a large scale for forage and has a good ability of self-sowing because of the high production of hard seeds (
<bibRefCitation id="0EF34AC91DCCBC05A1E107049ED77935" author="Gillett, JM" journalOrPublisher="Iowa State University Press, Ames, Iowa, USA" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B24" refString="Gillett, JM, Taylor, NL, 2001. The World of Clovers. Iowa State University Press, Ames, Iowa, USA" title="The World of Clovers." year="2001">Gillett and Taylor 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="43691049F05787E6B1C57172B3854ADE" author="Coulot, P" journalOrPublisher="Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B10" refString="Coulot, P, Rabaute, P, 2013. Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae. Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" title="Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae." year="2013">Coulot and Rabaute 2013</bibRefCitation>
). It was repeatedly cited by Italian botanists for central and southern Italy. However, its presence has probably been overestimated mainly in the past due either to the different taxonomical treatments of closely-related species or to confusion among them. In particular, we cannot confirm the species in Apulia, although it is indicated by 
<bibRefCitation id="FD91A5D1278CC1F0EE5823127E3EF9A0" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="7CD0F02E200697FDFA202E70341D7254" author="Tenore, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora Napolitana" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="151 - 152" refId="B53" refString="Tenore, M, 1835-1838. . Flora Napolitana 5: 151 - 152" volume="5" year="1835 - 1838">Tenore (1835-1838)</bibRefCitation>
reports it for Gargano where it is not confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="310250E98B6F2296EAAE3DC4BDBDC6B8" author="Licht, W" journalOrPublisher="Shaker Verlag, Aachen" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B31" refString="Licht, W, 2008. Bestimmungsschluessel zur Flora des Gargano (Sued-Italien). Shaker Verlag, Aachen" title="Bestimmungsschluessel zur Flora des Gargano (Sued-Italien)." year="2008">Licht (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional data come from 
<normalizedToken id="26D547BB19EB3A1F443FE6F2ABC54690" originalValue="Béguinot">Beguinot</normalizedToken>
(in 
<bibRefCitation id="C6C9BC58E1DA6F5742D761FACB204667" author="Fenaroli, L" journalOrPublisher="Webbia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="435 - 578" publicationUrl="10.1080/00837792.1970.10669916" refId="B16" refString="Fenaroli, L, 1970. Florae Garganicae Prodromus. Pars II. Webbia 24: 435 - 578" title="Florae Garganicae Prodromus. Pars II." url="10.1080/00837792.1970.10669916" volume="24" year="1970">Fenaroli 1970</bibRefCitation>
) but we were not able to find herbarium samples for the mentioned locality (Bosco Sfilzi). Concerning Basilicata, the indications from Balvano (Barbazita) and Muro Lucano (N. Terracciano), as well as the samples by Trotter (Gavioli 1848) could not be verified till now. 
<bibRefCitation id="22EAA6D61F7221C02A7EEB64EA6808C5" author="Gibelli, G" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="179 - 222" refId="B23" refString="Gibelli, G, Belli, S, 1892. Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p.p.). Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2) 42: 179 - 222" title="Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p. p.)." volume="42" year="1892">Gibelli and Belli (1892)</bibRefCitation>
identify a 
<taxonomicName id="39C9FE358B7E2F7E70F4212EFE610CE2" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. stenodictyon" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="stenodictyon">Trifolium vesiculosum var. stenodictyon</taxonomicName>
Gibelli &amp; Belli from Mt. Vulture, based on samples collected by Terracciano and Gussone, corresponding to intermediate forms (hybrids?) between 
<taxonomicName id="21F8AAA2A4A43F385A6ECA1F78C158CF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="70CC6A4C229726370C2B3513CFB292E1" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B3F6E9D06D25D5D0454A26D121062FEC" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis id="1389537C6D398177B551B75FA0A3B9A3" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="47CB3495573FCE530E1C793A4131079F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="E9D9EA84B9B3B6517569100B761D425A" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.str. is not confirmed either from the literature or by recent gatherings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E24B979A00686130EE86D12BD0323C8A" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="16" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">
This species is considered as occurring in Calabria by 
<bibRefCitation id="007EF35E5642BD14D315C058F72F4A0A" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, based on 
<bibRefCitation id="A0FAD19B19F41247088E46F451886DE2" author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, who assigned a specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="37A0C861082D9D1C7B1418744E0E30C5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis id="C87AD831E9B7F646751CCFF4B68C1C7E" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="15">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Fiumefreddo Bruzio (A. Fiori, 1899, FI!) to 
<taxonomicName id="71E08E2D11E6F2671A701894220FB2DD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="rumelicum">Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, for the same region there are also some old reports (
<bibRefCitation id="541744FDC48AC5B74932B68D03E11F15" author="Porta, P" journalOrPublisher="Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="224 - 290" refId="B46" refString="Porta, P, 1879. Viaggio botanico intrapreso da Huter, Porta e Rigo in Calabria nel 1877. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano 11: 224 - 290" title="Viaggio botanico intrapreso da Huter, Porta e Rigo in Calabria nel 1877." volume="11" year="1879">Porta 1879</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C74E76948907A5AF104BE21B57E81010" author="Macchiati, L" journalOrPublisher="Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="59 - 100" refId="B34" refString="Macchiati, L, 1884. Catalogo delle piante raccolte nei dintorni di Reggio Calabria dal Settembre 1881 al Febbraio 1883. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano 16: 59 - 100" title="Catalogo delle piante raccolte nei dintorni di Reggio Calabria dal Settembre 1881 al Febbraio 1883." volume="16" year="1884">Macchiati 1884</bibRefCitation>
) dating back 
<pageBreakToken id="18073B59285975702149960EA4685311" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" start="start">to</pageBreakToken>
a time when 
<taxonomicName id="A6C52B67B45A314B77BECA797D7AA3EF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabile">
<emphasis id="FA574260E8330BA88278A66FAD20C50F" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium mutabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="122C8CA679D7129D9CEF308099048DEA" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis id="D0E2D9667E1654AE839154F81C79AD68" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both currently occurring in Calabria, were considered as varieties of 
<taxonomicName id="B8579B1551BBD72434B33E7F8FE22210" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="438FB3577078EA3BA5FA2BC6339963B5" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, the latter species is here recorded as requiring confirmation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="78635847BC5FCC5F836B63B0FA5B5624" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">
The presence of the species by 
<bibRefCitation id="5FF4803E2FE03436DB2278C4273D5FC8" author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
in Sicily derives from 
<bibRefCitation id="E1BDF0E40355C790A1775793B8C1E289" author="Brullo, S" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino dell'Accademia Gioenia di Scienze Naturali in Catania" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" pagination="405 - 452" refId="B3" refString="Brullo, S, 1982. Le associazioni sub-nitrofile dell'Echio-Galactition tomentosae in Sicilia. Bollettino dell'Accademia Gioenia di Scienze Naturali in Catania 15: 405 - 452" title="Le associazioni sub-nitrofile dell'Echio-Galactition tomentosae in Sicilia." volume="15" year="1982">Brullo (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, who cites it in some phytosociological 
<normalizedToken id="48967423C758424223BA93389B633465" originalValue="relevés">releves</normalizedToken>
. It is also reported by 
<bibRefCitation id="52C98B184818DB53B0CC31945C753DD8" author="Gussone, G" journalOrPublisher="Ex Typis Tramater, Neapoli" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B27" refString="Gussone, G, 1843. Florae Siculae Synopsis. Ex Typis Tramater, Neapoli" title="Florae Siculae Synopsis" year="1843">Gussone (1843)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="99E160627A93DC22310D6BCE5E20928A" author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, but questioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="1D4C9FF57C0FAEAB315932D4E21DFFC2" author="La Rosa, A" journalOrPublisher="Universita degli Studi di Palermo" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B30" refString="La Rosa, A, 2011. Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia. Universita degli Studi di Palermo" title="Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia" year="2011">La Rosa (2011)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation id="DB9DF6D6D4CE026A3B4034659E832CD0" author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, who quote many references and state 
<normalizedToken id="019A4815596641FA8B4040075EBAEE7C" originalValue="“…">&quot;...</normalizedToken>
all localities of Southern Sicily are doubtful due perhaps to the limited identification made by the authors to the rank of species to 
<taxonomicName id="9C9D9844FB841BE16C8D53CD701D4500" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mutabile">
<emphasis id="40905A961F20313A5760EA0963557212" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium mutabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="C09CE33924770E4BB0BCD482E0D51010" authority="Savi" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subsp." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subspecies" species="vesiculosum" subspecies="mutabile">Trifolium vesiculosum Savi subsp. mutabile</taxonomicName>
Portenschl.&quot;. To the latter species we attribute the Sicilian reports of 
<taxonomicName id="DAC8EA9D1E6F9A50239EEFCB9F6AD450" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="9A0A07267B7FC1C20D3586896D8C8CDF" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the sample in CAT (http://www.dipbot.unict.it/herbarium/foto/06/006028.jpg) from 
<normalizedToken id="81CF538614F97C7CAD55E55D1D697232" originalValue="Cefalù">Cefalu</normalizedToken>
, clearly refers to 
<taxonomicName id="44A30FFCE1EDBE8E899BFD52176B013E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="9" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis id="2CFDCE12074514E05F5D762FADB08204" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="16">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and confirms the presence of the species, at least in the past.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
